<subSubSection pageNumber="699" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="699">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="699">Note:</emphasis>
Hitchcock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="699">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
12: 124. 1908) indicated 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sloane’s">Sloane's</normalizedToken>
specimen (HS 2: 7, BM-SL) as the type. Despite its close association with the published illustration, Linnaeus did not see the material and it is not original material for the name. Subsequently, Hitchcock (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="699">Contr. U. S. Natl. Herb.</emphasis>
17: 269. 1913) referred to &quot;the type specimen collected by Browne&quot; but without indicating where it was located. Formal typification on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Sloane’s">Sloane's</normalizedToken>
illustration was effected in Jarvis &amp; al.
</paragraph>
